  31. ‌#define ROTL32(x,n) ((x) << n | (x) >> (32-n))

  33. ‌#define MIX(h,d) \
  34.   d *= 0xcc9e2d51; \
  35.   d = ROTL32(d, 15); \
  36.   d *= 0x1b873593; \
  37.   h ^= d; \
  38.   h = ROTL32(h, 13); \
  39.   h = h * 5 + 0xe6546b64;

  41. ‌#define FINAL_MIX(h) \
  42.   h ^= h >> 16; \
  43.   h *= 0x85ebca6b; \
  44.   h ^= h >> 13; \
  45.   h *= 0xc2b2ae35; \
  46.   h ^= h >> 16;

  48. ‌CAMLexport uint32_t caml_hash_mix_uint32(uint32_t h, uint32_t d)

  51.   return h;

  54. /* Mix a platform-native integer. */

  56. ‌CAMLexport uint32_t caml_hash_mix_intnat(uint32_t h, intnat d)
  57. {
  58.   uint32_t n;
  59. #ifdef ARCH_SIXTYFOUR
  60.   /* Mix the low 32 bits and the high 32 bits, in a way that preserves
  61.      32/64 compatibility: we want n = (uint32_t) d
  62.      if d is in the range [-2^31, 2^31-1]. */
  63.   n = (d >> 32) ^ (d >> 63) ^ d;
  64.   /* If 0 <= d < 2^31:   d >> 32 = 0     d >> 63 = 0
  65.      If -2^31 <= d < 0:  d >> 32 = -1    d >> 63 = -1
  66.      In both cases, n = (uint32_t) d.  */
  67. #else
  68.   n = d;
  69. #endif
  70.   MIX(h, n);
  71.   return h;
  72. }

  74. /* Mix a 64-bit integer. */

  76. ‌CAMLexport uint32_t caml_hash_mix_int64(uint32_t h, int64_t d)
  77. {
  78.   uint32_t hi = (uint32_t) (d >> 32), lo = (uint32_t) d;
  79.   MIX(h, lo);
  80.   MIX(h, hi);
  81.   return h;
  82. }

  84. /* Mix a double-precision float.
  85.    Treats +0.0 and -0.0 identically.
  86.    Treats all NaNs identically.
  87. */

  89. ‌CAMLexport uint32_t caml_hash_mix_double(uint32_t hash, double d)
  90. {
  91.   union {
  92.     double d;
  93. #if defined(ARCH_BIG_ENDIAN) || (defined(__arm__) && !defined(__ARM_EABI__))
  94.     struct { uint32_t h; uint32_t l; } i;
  95. #else
  96.     struct { uint32_t l; uint32_t h; } i;
  97. #endif
  98.   } u;
  99.   uint32_t h, l;
  100.   /* Convert to two 32-bit halves */
  101.   u.d = d;
  102.   h = u.i.h; l = u.i.l;
  103.   /* Normalize NaNs */
  104.   if ((h & 0x7FF00000) == 0x7FF00000 && (l | (h & 0xFFFFF)) != 0) {
  105.     h = 0x7FF00000;
  106.     l = 0x00000001;
  107.   }
  108.   /* Normalize -0 into +0 */
  109.   else if (h == 0x80000000 && l == 0) {
  110.     h = 0;
  111.   }
  112.   MIX(hash, l);
  113.   MIX(hash, h);
  114.   return hash;
  115. }

  117. /* Mix a single-precision float.
  118.    Treats +0.0 and -0.0 identically.
  119.    Treats all NaNs identically.
  120. */

  122. ‌CAMLexport uint32_t caml_hash_mix_float(uint32_t hash, float d)
  123. {
  124.   union {
  125.     float f;
  126.     uint32_t i;
  127.   } u;
  128.   uint32_t n;
  129.   /* Convert to int32_t */
  130.   u.f = d;  n = u.i;
  131.   /* Normalize NaNs */
  132.   if ((n & 0x7F800000) == 0x7F800000 && (n & 0x007FFFFF) != 0) {
  133.     n = 0x7F800001;
  134.   }
  135.   /* Normalize -0 into +0 */
  136.   else if (n == 0x80000000) {
  137.     n = 0;
  138.   }
  139.   MIX(hash, n);
  140.   return hash;
  141. }

  143. /* Mix an OCaml string */

  145. ‌CAMLexport uint32_t caml_hash_mix_string(uint32_t h, value s)
  146. {
  147.   mlsize_t len = caml_string_length(s);
  148.   mlsize_t i;
  149.   uint32_t w;

  151.   /* Mix by 32-bit blocks (little-endian) */
  152.   for (i = 0; i + 4 <= len; i += 4) {
  153. #ifdef ARCH_BIG_ENDIAN
  154.     w = Byte_u(s, i)
  155.         | (Byte_u(s, i+1) << 8)
  156.         | (Byte_u(s, i+2) << 16)
  157.         | (Byte_u(s, i+3) << 24);
  158. #else
  159.     w = *((uint32_t *) &Byte_u(s, i));
  160. #endif
  161.     MIX(h, w);
  162.   }
  163.   /* Finish with up to 3 bytes */
  164.   w = 0;
  165.   switch (len & 3) {
  166.   case 3: w  = Byte_u(s, i+2) << 16;   /* fallthrough */
  167.   case 2: w |= Byte_u(s, i+1) << 8;    /* fallthrough */
  168.   case 1: w |= Byte_u(s, i);
  169.           MIX(h, w);
  170.   default: /*skip*/;     /* len & 3 == 0, no extra bytes, do nothing */
  171.   }
  172.   /* Finally, mix in the length.  Ignore the upper 32 bits, generally 0. */
  173.   h ^= (uint32_t) len;
  174.   return h;
  175. }

  177. /* Maximal size of the queue used for breadth-first traversal.  */
  178. ‌#define HASH_QUEUE_SIZE 256
  179. /* Maximal number of Forward_tag links followed in one step */
  180. ‌#define MAX_FORWARD_DEREFERENCE 1000

  182. /* The generic hash function */

  184. ‌CAMLprim value caml_hash(value count, value limit, value seed, value obj)
  185. {
  186.   value queue[HASH_QUEUE_SIZE]; /* Queue of values to examine */
  187.   intnat rd;                    /* Position of first value in queue */
  188.   intnat wr;                    /* One past position of last value in queue */
  189.   intnat sz;                    /* Max number of values to put in queue */
  190.   intnat num;                   /* Max number of meaningful values to see */
  191.   uint32_t h;                     /* Rolling hash */
  192.   value v;
  193.   mlsize_t i, len;

  195.   sz = Long_val(limit);
  196.   if (sz < 0 || sz > HASH_QUEUE_SIZE) sz = HASH_QUEUE_SIZE;
  197.   num = Long_val(count);
  198.   h = Int_val(seed);
  199.   queue[0] = obj; rd = 0; wr = 1;

  201.   while (rd < wr && num > 0) {
  202.     v = queue[rd++];
  203.   again:
  204.     if (Is_long(v)) {
  205.       h = caml_hash_mix_intnat(h, v);
  206.       num--;
  207.     } else {
  208.       switch (Tag_val(v)) {
  209.       case String_tag:
  210.         h = caml_hash_mix_string(h, v);
  211.         num--;
  212.         break;
  213.       case Double_tag:
  214.         h = caml_hash_mix_double(h, Double_val(v));
  215.         num--;
  216.         break;
  217.       case Double_array_tag:
  218.         for (i = 0, len = Wosize_val(v) / Double_wosize; i < len; i++) {
  219.           h = caml_hash_mix_double(h, Double_flat_field(v, i));
  220.           num--;
  221.           if (num <= 0) break;
  222.         }
  223.         break;
  224.       case Abstract_tag:
  225.         /* Block contents unknown.  Do nothing. */
  226.         break;
  227.       case Infix_tag:
  228.         /* Mix in the offset to distinguish different functions from
  229.            the same mutually-recursive definition */
  230.         h = caml_hash_mix_uint32(h, Infix_offset_val(v));
  231.         v = v - Infix_offset_val(v);
  232.         goto again;
  233.       case Forward_tag:
  234.         /* PR#6361: we can have a loop here, so limit the number of
  235.            Forward_tag links being followed */
  236.         for (i = MAX_FORWARD_DEREFERENCE; i > 0; i--) {
  237.           v = Forward_val(v);
  238.           if (Is_long(v) || Tag_val(v) != Forward_tag)
  239.             goto again;
  240.         }
  241.         /* Give up on this object and move to the next */
  242.         break;
  243.       case Object_tag:
  244.         h = caml_hash_mix_intnat(h, Oid_val(v));
  245.         num--;
  246.         break;
  247.       case Custom_tag:
  248.         /* If no hashing function provided, do nothing. */
  249.         /* Only use low 32 bits of custom hash, for 32/64 compatibility */
  250.         if (Custom_ops_val(v)->hash != NULL) {
  251.           uint32_t n = (uint32_t) Custom_ops_val(v)->hash(v);
  252.           h = caml_hash_mix_uint32(h, n);
  253.           num--;
  254.         }
  255.         break;
  256.       case Closure_tag: {
  257.         mlsize_t startenv;
  258.         len = Wosize_val(v);
  259.         startenv = Start_env_closinfo(Closinfo_val(v));
  260.         CAMLassert (startenv <= len);
  261.         /* Mix in the tag and size, but do not count this towards [num] */
  262.         h = caml_hash_mix_uint32(h, Cleanhd_hd(Hd_val(v)));
  263.         /* Mix the code pointers, closure info fields, and infix headers */
  264.         for (i = 0; i < startenv; i++) {
  265.           h = caml_hash_mix_intnat(h, Field(v, i));
  266.           num--;
  267.         }
  268.         /* Copy environment fields into queue,
  269.            not exceeding the total size [sz] */
  270.         for (/*nothing*/; i < len; i++) {
  271.           if (wr >= sz) break;
  272.           queue[wr++] = Field(v, i);
  273.         }
  274.         break;
  275.       }
  276.       case Cont_tag:
  277.         /* All continuations hash to the same value,
  278.            since we have no idea how to distinguish them. */
  279.         break;

  281.       default:
  282.         /* Mix in the tag and size, but do not count this towards [num] */
  283.         h = caml_hash_mix_uint32(h, Cleanhd_hd(Hd_val(v)));
  284.         /* Copy fields into queue, not exceeding the total size [sz] */
  285.         for (i = 0, len = Wosize_val(v); i < len; i++) {
  286.           if (wr >= sz) break;
  287.           queue[wr++] = Field(v, i);
  288.         }
  289.         break;
  290.       }
  291.     }
  292.   }
  293.   /* Final mixing of bits */
  294.   FINAL_MIX(h);
  295.   /* Fold result to the range [0, 2^30-1] so that it is a nonnegative
  296.      OCaml integer both on 32 and 64-bit platforms. */
  297.   return Val_int(h & 0x3FFFFFFFU);
  298. }

  300. ‌CAMLprim value caml_string_hash(value seed, value string)
  301. {
  302.   uint32_t h;
  303.   h = Int_val(seed);
  304.   h = caml_hash_mix_string (h, string);
  305.   FINAL_MIX(h);
  306.   return Val_int(h & 0x3FFFFFFFU);
  307. }

  309. /* Hashing variant tags */

  311. ‌CAMLexport value caml_hash_variant(char const * tag)
  312. {
  313.   value accu;
  314.   /* Same hashing algorithm as in ../typing/btype.ml, function hash_variant */
  315.   for (accu = Val_int(0); *tag != 0; tag++)
  316.     accu = Val_int(223 * Int_val(accu) + *((unsigned char *) tag));
  317. #ifdef ARCH_SIXTYFOUR
  318.   accu = accu & Val_long(0x7FFFFFFFL);
  319. #endif
  320.   /* Force sign extension of bit 31 for compatibility between 32 and 64-bit
  321.      platforms */
  322.   return (int32_t) accu;
  323. }
